The implementation I provided handles all the specified control policy requirements:
1. **Boot**: Heater starts OFF in SAFE_OFF state
2. **TEMP < 47**: Turns heater ON (HEATING state)
3. **TEMP > 52**: Turns heater OFF (SAFE_OFF state)  
4. **47 <= TEMP < 50**: Holds previous actuator state (HOLDING state)
5. **50 <= TEMP <= 52 with rising temp**: Early anticipatory OFF (HOLDING state)
6. **50 <= TEMP <= 52 without rising**: Holds previous actuator state (HOLDING state)
7. **Malformed input / sensor timeout**: Forces heater OFF (SAFE_OFF)
8. **Stale data > 1000ms**: Forces heater OFF (SAFE_OFF)
